          "description": "Dr. Bard is terrific. She is highly professional, courteous and prompt. I was a little nervous since I hadn't been checked in a long time. Both she and the office made me comfortable and  generously shared knowledge and answered questions.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURXdXU3WE93EAE!2m1!1s0x0:0x8469d5f6b02876e3!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgIDWuu7XOw%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "4 years ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2022-03-21T23:11:42+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Justine Oddo",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "110414790045464124825",
          "user_review_count": 2,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfTGi7OzFuO5CF32H8jTJVJc3rn4SbN6-8sx_c-x0k9nqc3YDq=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "When looking for a new dermatologist,  a friend of mine highly recommended Dr Susan Bard so I went to Dr Bard for full body annual mole check.  Dr. Bard was excellent. She was very thorough in checking and even did a very good job at checking my scalp under my long hair.  Dr Bard was very open and honest in our conversation.  She asked if I had any concerns and she immediately answered my questions with thoughtful responses.  I could tell by her answers, that she is highly intelligent and is very experienced.   Excellent bedside manner!   I felt very comfortable in her office and having a conversation with her.  She took a genuine interest in my health.\n\nThe office was pleasant. The receptionist was super friendly and a pleasure to check in with.  I could tell she was genuine in welcoming me and making me feel comfortable in the office.  Even though I was there for a medical check up, there was  information displayed in the office about aesthetic and cosmetic skin procedures so that was interesting in a good way\u2026.. a thought for another visit.\n\nI highly recommend Dr. Susan Bard. I will definitely be going back to her and using her as my dermatologist.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURXMnZ6UHF3RRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x8469d5f6b02876e3!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgIDW2vzPqwE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "4 years ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2022-03-21T17:40:47+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Beth W.",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "110632503040557655204",
          "user_review_count": 36,
          "user_photo_count": 12,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU7yATbMfdu62KAE2aoGAQuOzcob7vDs7NL69zkD-_1NqxB29_l=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "For my 4 month acne treatment with Dr. Bard, I found the service very unimpressive. First, the doctor would not answer any question for prescription after the appointments, which costed $250 out-of-pocket and took the doctor 2 mins to run through. Second, one time the pharmacy needed the prescriber's double confirmation for my Accutane, I called her office many times to remind Dr. Bard to do two click on her end. She didn't get back to me until 10 days later and I needed to waited another month for the compliance to get my medicine. In the end, I switched to a dermatologist on the Park Ave., who quotes a fraction of what Dr. Bard charges me and is super efficient and responsive with my medication.\n\nPlus, her office promised to submit claims for my out-of-network benefit. But on my insurance, I never saw Dr. bard submit those claims for me.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUR4LWRfLVNBEAE!2m1!1s0x0:0x8469d5f6b02876e3!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgIDx-d_-SA%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "3 years ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2023-06-11T21:20:27+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Abigail George",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "113216277483829151641",
          "user_review_count": 1,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJG_enGcbMMF2cuNHe6fyI0Hlq9a6Sx4kqOVKxeexI-BOLXcA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "Terrible, awful experience. I went in for a cyst removal so two separate encounters with Dr. Bard (one for the consultation and then the procedure itself). The first time I saw her, I waited 30 minutes in the patient room before she saw me. She rushed through my consultation and took less than 5 minutes. During my procedure, she did not allow time for questions, did not provide a thorough explanation and rushed through the whole process, zero bedside manner. And it gets worse: her phone rung FOUR times and not once did she silence the ringer. As she is cutting into my head, Dr. Bard and her medical assistant are bickering back and forth-- the medical assistant questioning the Dr. and the Dr. scolding her back -- completely unprofessional and uncomfortable. After she sews me up, she leaves the room without saying anything and does not provide any info on aftercare. A very weird and excruciating experience. I definitely do NOT recommend this doctor or the office - the reception staff are extremely unhelpful as well.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNHdXVEQmNBEAE!2m1!1s0x0:0x8469d5f6b02876e3!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgICGuuDBcA%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "4 years ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2021-10-26T21:49:22+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Emily Schoenfeld",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "106068777603932534513",
          "user_review_count": 4,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIVKwGPFnH5TVofHmwmuKGZ0_bpHE4m27qYqynoSGYknfYfiw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "Receptionists are very sweet. Unfortunately Doctor refuses to answer questions or concerns about prescription medications over the phone. Once the visit is over, if you want to ask the Doctor a question about your medication, you have to pay for another appointment.\n\nUpdate: After I left the one star review I received a bill from Dr. Susan Bard for $1,900 for a simple Cryotherpay in one small location which she wrote on the bill as \"surgery.\" Was in the office for a total of 5-minutes. Called office to inquire what their normal billing rates are for such a treatment and was told I would have to pay for a consultation again with Dr. Susan Bard to simply find out what her range of typical prices are for this treatment. Truly a greedy practice.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNjOEtMd3NRRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x8469d5f6b02876e3!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgICc8KLwsQE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "Edited 5 years ago",
